<br>
... she also notices Zildrax. With a yelp of terror, she skitters backwards and, in one fell swoop, manages to knock over her mug of mead, fall off of her stool, and get tangled in the legs of said stool. With a muttered curse, she momentarily forgets the presence of the Iksar in leiu of more painful experiences - namely, the back of her head. She yanks off her helmet and touches tentative fingers to her scalp, and pulls them back to see them covered in blood.  With a muttered curse, she wipes the blood off on a patch of her thick leather skirt, and her eyes trail slowly from her knees...  to her feet...  to the scaly claw tapping ever-so-gently on the wooden floor.<br>
<br>
Everything else rushes back to her, and she looks up, what seems to her, in extraordinarily slow motion with eyes that are suddenly filled with terror at the lizard-like humanoid that looks amusedly down at her.  She creeps backwards, hands that are normally so steady in battle now trembling as she seeks purchase in the floor beneath her so that she can get away.  Behind the bar, out the door, up the stairs, it does not matter.  All that is important now is OUT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 580<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/1/02 1:03:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alternate reaction to Zildrax</span><hr size=1> Zildrax laughs as he watches the soft skin skittering about. If only they all reacted like that. What was more of a shame was that in this bar her fear served very little purpose, it did nothing to further Thule's will. Zildrax had agreed long ago not to start fights here. Realizing that, he spoke.<br>
<br>
&quot;I will not harm you here, soft skin. I made that agreement long ago. As much as I enjoy seeing you panic, it has no purpose beyond mild entertainment. You may stop.&quot; <br>
<br>
Zildrax folded his arms, silently wishing again that all his enemies reacted to his presence like that. <p><img src="http://members.aol.com/bseh42/images/zilsig.jpg"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A> at: 8/1/02 1:07:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uamaeliya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amaeliya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/1/02 3:39:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alternate reaction to Zildrax</span><hr size=1> ((Aww....  *pouts*))<br>
